NAME
  ls - list directory contents

SYNOPSIS
  ls [OPTION]... [FILE]...

DESCRIPTION
  List information about the specified files, or the current working directory by default.
	
	Default options can be set in LS_OPTIONS environment variable.

OPTIONS
  -a
    do not ignore entries starting with .
  -l
    use a long listing format
  -s
    display file sizes
  -si
		use 1000 instead of 1024 for size calculations
	-h
		human readable file sizes (K, M, G)
  -p
    append / indicator to directories
  -M
    display Microsoft-style file and directory count after listing

EXAMPLES
  ls
    Displays the contents of the current directory.

  ls /bin /mnt
    Displays the contents of the `/bin`/ and `/mnt` directories, one after the other.